{
  "stem": "18770.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Incredible experience-- I mean, we stay at the Metropol Hotel, which is still there, I'm told.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It's one of those hotels from czarist Russian days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I've never seen a place that big.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We keep, keep getting lost-- the kids.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We played there to see if we can find certain stairs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Like, there's one stairwell where there is the big stuffed bear on its hind paws.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We go looking for that, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The hotel seems so big to us that we look for, for hours before we can find that particular staircase.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My sister-- this I love-- my sister reads us-- me and-- my cousins and myself sit around.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she will read us in Polish in Moscow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They-- that's, that's sort of also the story of the war, the dislocation, the movement, you know, the mixing of things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So here we're being read a British author, 19th-century author, in a Russian capital in Polish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And-- but I remember taking walks with my father in Red Square.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember, you know, the child's sense of it being huge and vast with those cupolas, you know, for the churches and-- I mean, those-- you know, the Byzantine, Greek-Orthodox style of architecture they have there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We're there for a bunch of weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We're there for some weeks, again, probably waiting for transit papers or train things to come through.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's becoming less dreadful because we are out-- I think there's a sense that we're out of Hitler's grasp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you must understand this is before anybody knows anything about concentration camps or, you know, or mass-- but everybody knows-- the Jews have known for a long time that Hitler is very bad news.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Russians are not pursuing at that point any specific anti-Jewish program.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
